@charsyam I think the best approach would be to allow user to pass in either a base `auth_url` without a path (e.g. `https://192.168.100.100`) or a full `auth_url` with a path (e.g. `http://192.168.100.100/v1.0/auth`, `http://192.168.100.100/`).

If user passes in just a base url, default auth path is appended to it, otherwise, the url is used directly the way it's passed in.

This also makes more sense, since currently the variable is called `auth_url` and now `base_auth_url` so you would expect you can pass in a whole url with a path.
